ARGUMENT

| Step | Hyp | Ref | Expression |
|---|---|---|---|

| 1 |  | #P_aev | |- ( A. x x = y -> A. z z = x ) |
| 2 |  | #P_ax-c16 | |- ( A. x x = y -> ( ph -> A. x ph ) ) |
| 3 |  | #P_biidd | |- ( A. z z = x -> ( ph <-> ph ) ) |
| 4 | 3 | #P_dral1 | |- ( A. z z = x -> ( A. z ph <-> A. x ph ) ) |
| 5 | 4 | #P_biimprd | |- ( A. z z = x -> ( A. x ph -> A. z ph ) ) |
| 6 | 1, 2, 5 | #P_sylsyld | |- ( A. x x = y -> ( ph -> A. z ph ) ) |
\
 A generalization of axiom ~ ax-c16 .  Version of ~ axc16g using ~ ax-c11 .  (Contributed by NM, 15-May-1993.)  (Proof shortened by Andrew Salmon, 25-May-2011.)  (Proof modification is discouraged.) (New usage is discouraged.)
